igure-apps/file-schema/wcf/servicedebug.md) element to the [\\&lt;behavior\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/behavior-of-endpointbehaviors.md) element from step 2 and enable or disable the various properties appropriate to your scenario.  \n  \n For a specific example, see the Example section.","nodes":[{"pos":[0,314],"content":"Use the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> properties from a configuration file or programmatically to enable the flow of managed exception information to the client for debugging purposes as well as the publication of HTML information files for users browsing the service in Web browsers.","nodes":[{"content":"Use the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior&gt;</ph> properties from a configuration file or programmatically to enable the flow of managed exception information to the client for debugging purposes as well as the publication of HTML information files for users browsing the service in Web browsers.","pos":[0,314],"source":"Use the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> properties from a configuration file or programmatically to enable the flow of managed exception information to the client for debugging purposes as well as the publication of HTML information files for users browsing the service in Web browsers."}]},{"pos":[321,589],"content":"Set the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.IncludeExceptionDetailInFaults%2A&gt;</ph> property to <ph id=\"ph2\">`true`</ph> to instruct <ph id=\"ph3\">[!INCLUDE[indigo2](~/includes/indigo2-md.md)]</ph> to return managed exception information in SOAP faults to clients for debugging purposes.","source":"Set the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.IncludeExceptionDetailInFaults%2A> property to `true` to instruct [!INCLUDE[indigo2](~/includes/indigo2-md.md)] to return managed exception information in SOAP faults to clients for deb