viceModel.Description.IServiceBehavior.Validate(System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDescription,System.ServiceModel.ServiceHostBase)\"&gt;&lt;/xref&gt;</ph> method to support the behavior.","source":"Implements the <xref href=\"System.ServiceModel.Description.IServiceBehavior.Validate(System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDescription,System.ServiceModel.ServiceHostBase)\"></xref> method to support the behavior."}],"pos":[39353,39567],"yaml":true},{"content":"The service description.","nodes":[{"pos":[0,24],"content":"The service description.","nodes":[{"content":"The service description.","pos":[0,24]}]}],"pos":[39860,39885],"yaml":true},{"content":"The service host.","nodes":[{"pos":[0,17],"content":"The service host.","nodes":[{"content":"The service host.","pos":[0,17]}]}],"pos":[39978,39996],"yaml":true}],"content":"### YamlMime:ManagedReference\nitems:\n- uid: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior\n  commentId: T:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior\n  id: ServiceDebugBehavior\n  children:\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.#ctor\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageBinding\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageEnabled\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageUrl\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageBinding\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageEnabled\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageUrl\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.IncludeExceptionDetailInFaults\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.System#ServiceModel#Description#IServiceBehavior#AddBindingParameters(System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDescription,System.ServiceModel.ServiceHostBase,System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection{System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceEndpoint},System.ServiceModel.Channels.BindingParameterCollection)\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.System#ServiceModel#Description#IServiceBehavior#ApplyDispatchBehavior(System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDescription,System.ServiceModel.ServiceHostBase)\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.System#ServiceModel#Description#IServiceBehavior#Validate(System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDescription,System.ServiceModel.ServiceHostBase)\n  langs:\n  - csharp\n  name: ServiceDebugBehavior\n  nameWithType: ServiceDebugBehavior\n  fullName: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior\n  type: Class\n  assemblies:\n  - System.ServiceModel\n  namespace: System.ServiceModel.Description\n  summary: Enables debugging and help information features for a Windows Communication Foundation (WCF) service.\n  remarks: \"Use the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> properties from a configuration file or programmatically to enable the flow of managed exception information to the client for debugging purposes as well as the publication of HTML information files for users browsing the service in Web browsers.  \\n  \\n Set the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.IncludeExceptionDetailInFaults%2A> property to `true` to instruct [!INCLUDE[indigo2](~/includes/indigo2-md.md)] to return managed exception information in SOAP faults to clients for debugging purposes.  \\n  \\n> [!CAUTION]\\n>  Returning managed exception information to clients can be a security risk because exception details expose information about the internal service implementation that could be used by unauthorized clients. In addition, although the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> properties can also be set programmatically, it can be easy to forget to disable <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.IncludeExceptionDetailInFaults%2A> when deploying.  \\n  \\n Because of the security issues involved, it is strongly recommended that:  \\n  \\n-   You use an application configuration file to set the value of the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.IncludeExceptionDetailInFaults%2A> property to `true`.  \\n  \\n-   You only do so only in controlled debugging scenarios.  \\n  \\n [!INCLUDE[crabout](~/includes/crabout-md.md)] the security issues related to managed exception information, see [Specifying and Handling Faults in Contracts and Services](~/docs/framework/wcf/specifying-and-handling-faults-in-contracts-and-services.md).  \\n  \\n The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageEnabled%2A> and <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageEnabled%2A> properties instruct the service to publish HTML help files when the service is viewed using an HTML browser.  \\n  \\n The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageUrl%2A> and <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageUrl%2A> properties control the location of the HTML help page that is viewed.  \\n  \\n To enable or disable one of the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> features using a configuration file:  \\n  \\n1.  Add a `behaviorConfiguration` attribute to the [\\\\&lt;service\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/service.md) element for your [!INCLUDE[indigo2](~/includes/indigo2-md.md)] service. Endpoint behaviors are configured on [\\\\<endpoint>](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/13aa23b7-2f08-4add-8dbf-a99f8127c017) elements; service behaviors on [\\\\&lt;service\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/service.md) elements.  \\n  \\n2.  Add to or create a [\\\\&lt;serviceBehaviors\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/servicebehaviors.md) section and add a [\\\\&lt;behavior\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/behavior-of-endpointbehaviors.md) element to that with the name that matches the `behaviorConfiguration` attribute value from step 1. Endpoint behaviors are configured using an [\\\\&lt;endpointBehaviors\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/endpointbehaviors.md) element; service behaviors are configured using a [\\\\&lt;serviceBehaviors\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/servicebehaviors.md) element.  \\n  \\n3.  Add a [\\\\&lt;serviceDebug\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/servicedebug.md) element to the [\\\\&lt;behavior\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/behavior-of-endpointbehaviors.md) element from step 2 and enable or disable the various properties appropriate to your scenario.  \\n  \\n For a specific example, see the Example section.\"\n  example:\n  - \"The following code example shows how to use a configuration file to enable the HTML help page feature and return exception information inside a SOAP fault back to the client for debugging purposes, in addition to enabling metadata support. This configuration file shows the following basic steps to adding support for the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> features:  \\n  \\n-   Because the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> type is an <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.IServiceBehavior?displayProperty=fullName> implementation, the [\\\\&lt;service\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/service.md) element that represents the service type has a behavior configuration identifier of `behaviorConfiguration=\\\"metadataAndDebug\\\"`.  \\n  \\n-   Because the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> type is an <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.IServiceBehavior?displayProperty=fullName> implementation a [\\\\&lt;behavior\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/behavior-of-endpointbehaviors.md) element is added to a [\\\\&lt;serviceBehaviors\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/servicebehaviors.md) section. Set the `name` attribute of the [\\\\&lt;behavior\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/behavior-of-endpointbehaviors.md) element the value of which is the identifier of the `behaviorConfiguration` attribute of the [\\\\&lt;service\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/service.md) element. In this case, the value is `metadataAndDebug`.  \\n  \\n-   Add a [\\\\&lt;serviceDebug\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/servicedebug.md) element with the various attributes set to the desired configuration. In this case, the `httpHelpPageEnabled` and `includeExceptionDetailInFaults` attribute values are set to `true`.  \\n  \\n [!code-xml[ServiceDebugBehaviorConfig#1](~/samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_CFX/servicedebugbehaviorconfig/cs/hostapplication.exe.config#1)]\"\n  syntax:\n    content: 'public class ServiceDebugBehavior : System.ServiceModel.Description.IServiceBehavior'\n  inheritance:\n  - System.Object\n  implements:\n  - System.ServiceModel.Description.IServiceBehavior\n  inheritedMembers:\n  - System.Object.Equals(System.Object)\n  - System.Object.Equals(System.Object,System.Object)\n  - System.Object.GetHashCode\n  - System.Object.GetType\n  - System.Object.MemberwiseClone\n  - System.Object.ReferenceEquals(System.Object,System.Object)\n  - System.Object.ToString\n  version:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  monikers:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  content_git_url: https://github.com/dotnet/docs/blob/master/xml/System.ServiceModel.Description/ServiceDebugBehavior.xml\n  ms.technology:\n  - dotnet-standard\n  author: Erikre\n  ms.author: erikre\n  manager: erikre\n- uid: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.#ctor\n  commentId: M:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.#ctor\n  id: '#ctor'\n  parent: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior\n  langs:\n  - csharp\n  name: ServiceDebugBehavior()\n  nameWithType: ServiceDebugBehavior.ServiceDebugBehavior()\n  fullName: ServiceDebugBehavior.ServiceDebugBehavior()\n  type: Constructor\n  assemblies:\n  - System.ServiceModel\n  namespace: System.ServiceModel.Description\n  summary: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href=\"System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior\"></xref> class.\n  remarks: \"The constructor creates a <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> object with the following defaults:  \\n  \\n-   The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.IncludeExceptionDetailInFaults%2A> property is `false`.  \\n  \\n-   The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageEnabled%2A> property is `true`.  \\n  \\n-   The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageEnabled%2A> property is `true`.  \\n  \\n-   The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageUrl%2A> property is the base address of the service that supports HTTP requests.  \\n  \\n-   The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageUrl%2A> is the base address of the service that supports HTTPS requests.\"\n  syntax:\n    content: public ServiceDebugBehavior ();\n    parameters: []\n  overload: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.#ctor*\n  exceptions: []\n  version:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  monikers:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  content_git_url: https://github.com/dotnet/docs/blob/master/xml/System.ServiceModel.Description/ServiceDebugBehavior.xml\n  ms.technology:\n  - dotnet-standard\n  author: Erikre\n  ms.author: erikre\n  manager: erikre\n- uid: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageBinding\n  commentId: P:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageBinding\n  id: HttpHelpPageBinding\n  parent: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior\n  langs:\n  - csharp\n  name: HttpHelpPageBinding\n  nameWithType: ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageBinding\n  fullName: ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageBinding\n  type: Property\n  assemblies:\n  - System.ServiceModel\n  namespace: System.ServiceModel.Description\n  summary: Gets or sets high-level access to the definition of a binding.\n  syntax:\n    content: public System.ServiceModel.Channels.Binding HttpHelpPageBinding { get; set; }\n    return:\n      type: System.ServiceModel.Channels.Binding\n      description: A channel binding.\n  overload: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageBinding*\n  exceptions: []\n  version:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  monikers:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  content_git_url: https://github.com/dotnet/docs/blob/master/xml/System.ServiceModel.Description/ServiceDebugBehavior.xml\n  ms.technology:\n  - dotnet-standard\n  author: Erikre\n  ms.author: erikre\n  manager: erikre\n- uid: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageEnabled\n  commentId: P:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageEnabled\n  id: HttpHelpPageEnabled\n  parent: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior\n  langs:\n  - csharp\n  name: HttpHelpPageEnabled\n  nameWithType: ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageEnabled\n  fullName: ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageEnabled\n  type: Property\n  assemblies:\n  - System.ServiceModel\n  namespace: System.ServiceModel.Description\n  summary: Gets or sets a value that controls whether [!INCLUDE[indigo1](~/includes/indigo1-md.md)] publishes an HTML help page at the address controlled by the <xref href=\"System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageUrl\"></xref> property.\n  remarks: \"Set the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageEnabled%2A> property to `false` to disable the publication of an HTML help page visible to HTML browsers.  \\n  \\n To ensure the HTML help page is published at the location controlled by the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageUrl%2A> property, you must set this property to `true` and then one of the following conditions must also be true:  \\n  \\n-   The <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageUrl%2A> property is an absolute address that supports the HTTP protocol scheme.  \\n  \\n-   There is a base address for the service that supports the HTTP protocol scheme.  \\n  \\n Although an exception is thrown if an absolute address that does not support the HTTP protocol scheme is assigned to the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageUrl%2A> property, any other scenario in which neither of the preceding criteria is met results in no exception and no HTML help page.\"\n  example:\n  - \"The following code example shows how to use a configuration file to enable the HTML help page feature and return exception information inside a SOAP fault back to the client for debugging purposes. This configuration file shows the following basic steps to adding support for the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> features:  \\n  \\n-   Because the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> type is a <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.IServiceBehavior?displayProperty=fullName> implementation, the [\\\\&lt;service\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/service.md) element that represents the service type has a behavior configuration identifier of `behaviorConfiguration=\\\"metadataAndDebug\\\"`.  \\n  \\n-   Again, because the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior> type is an <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.IServiceBehavior?displayProperty=fullName> implementation a [\\\\&lt;behavior\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/behavior-of-endpointbehaviors.md) element is added to a [\\\\&lt;serviceBehaviors\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/servicebehaviors.md) section. The `name` attribute of the [\\\\&lt;behavior\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/behavior-of-endpointbehaviors.md) element the value of which is the identifier of the `behaviorConfiguration` attribute of the [\\\\&lt;service\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/service.md) element. In this case, the value is `metadataAndDebug`.  \\n  \\n-   Add a [\\\\&lt;serviceDebug\\\\&gt;](~/docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/servicedebug.md) element with the various attributes set to the desired configuration. In this case, the `httpHelpPageEnabled` and `includeExceptionDetailInFaults` attribute values are set to `true`.  \\n  \\n [!code-xml[ServiceDebugBehaviorConfig#1](~/samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_CFX/servicedebugbehaviorconfig/cs/hostapplication.exe.config#1)]\"\n  syntax:\n    content: public bool HttpHelpPageEnabled { get; set; }\n    return:\n      type: System.Boolean\n      description: '`true` if [!INCLUDE[indigo2](~/includes/indigo2-md.md)] publishes an HTML help page; otherwise, `false`. The default is `true`.'\n  overload: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageEnabled*\n  exceptions: []\n  attributes: []\n  version:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  monikers:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  content_git_url: https://github.com/dotnet/docs/blob/master/xml/System.ServiceModel.Description/ServiceDebugBehavior.xml\n  ms.technology:\n  - dotnet-standard\n  author: Erikre\n  ms.author: erikre\n  manager: erikre\n- uid: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageUrl\n  commentId: P:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageUrl\n  id: HttpHelpPageUrl\n  parent: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior\n  langs:\n  - csharp\n  name: HttpHelpPageUrl\n  nameWithType: ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageUrl\n  fullName: ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageUrl\n  type: Property\n  assemblies:\n  - System.ServiceModel\n  namespace: System.ServiceModel.Description\n  summary: Gets or sets the location at which the HTML help file is published.\n  remarks: \"Use the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageUrl%2A> property to enable the use of a custom HTML help file that is returned from an HTTP/Get request such as that of an HTML browser. The location of the HTML help file is resolved as follows:  \\n  \\n-   If the value of this property is a relative address, then the location of the HTML help file is the value of the service base address that supports HTTP requests plus this property value.  \\n  \\n-   If the value of this property is an absolute address and supports HTTP requests, then the location of the HTML help file is the value of this property.  \\n  \\n-   If the value of this property is absolute but does not support HTTP requests, an exception is thrown.  \\n  \\n This property is applied only in the case that the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageEnabled%2A> property is `true`.\"\n  syntax:\n    content: >-\n      [System.ComponentModel.TypeConverter(typeof(System.UriTypeConverter))]\n\n      public Uri HttpHelpPageUrl { get; set; }\n    return:\n      type: System.Uri\n      description: The relative or absolute HTTP-based URL of the custom HTML help file that the user sees when the endpoint is viewed using an HTML browser.\n  overload: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpHelpPageUrl*\n  exceptions: []\n  attributes:\n  - type: System.ComponentModel.TypeConverterAttribute\n  version:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  monikers:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  content_git_url: https://github.com/dotnet/docs/blob/master/xml/System.ServiceModel.Description/ServiceDebugBehavior.xml\n  ms.technology:\n  - dotnet-standard\n  author: Erikre\n  ms.author: erikre\n  manager: erikre\n- uid: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageBinding\n  commentId: P:System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageBinding\n  id: HttpsHelpPageBinding\n  parent: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugBehavior\n  langs:\n  - csharp\n  name: HttpsHelpPageBinding\n  nameWithType: ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageBinding\n  fullName: ServiceDebugBehavior.HttpsHelpPageBinding\n  type: Property\n  assemblies:\n  - System.ServiceModel\n  namespace: System.ServiceModel.Description\n  summary: Gets or sets high-level access to the definition of a binding.\n  syntax:\n    content: public System.ServiceModel.Channels.Binding HttpsHelpPageBinding { get; set; }\n    return:\n      type: System.ServiceModel.Channels.Binding\n      description: A channel binding.\n  overload: System.ServiceModel.Description.ServiceDebugB